##Diary of the siege of Wuhan | Day thirty-seven

Techread

Features, Lanxi, founder of zhulu.com  , focuses on in-depth observations and business reviews of Internet startups, new media, and subcultures.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Many say they would like to have the diary published on those days, but that is impossible under the current censorship regime, including online electronic channels.

When this is over, I will find other ways to organize and preserve the complete text of the collection, and I will provide reasonable access to the program, there is no hurry.

"beyond the plan" may be something we all have in common this winter, just as I didn't expect my diary to be kept for so long, or that my housebound life would be so depressing, i didn't expect to see an outbreak of a new epidemic in the central district, and I didn't expect to eat instant noodles so intensively again many years after I graduated from college..

Many people's plans were disrupted, and there were even news reports of a cruel couple whose parents were unable to go out to work because of the epidemic, who had no income and no savings at the same time, and who were forced to abandon their newborn baby in a hospital, and ridiculous.

As a starting point for the 2020s, the run up wasn't so bad. I'd heard enough signals that the good times weren't going to last, and I was ready to fall, only to find that I'd fallen from the roof, the band-aid in my pocket is useless. I need a cast.

Well, this is fucked up.

The weather in Wuhan began to overcast, thick clouds floating above the buildings, erasing the colors and details of the light, even the grass and trees were covered with a Wabi ash-like net, bleak Sabi Sabi.

Every day I open the Meituan and ele.me interface, there is an experience of opening a box in the game, I don't know which stores are open, if there happen to be some stores I like on the list, that's as surprising as pulling out a SSR.

A few days ago with Baidu index limits Wuhan area, checked the search heat change of a few key words, very vivid reflected the life condition of Wuhan citizen, Paste Data Again:

- Bread: 260 per cent increase in search peak over average;

- pickled mustard tuber: search peak is 343% higher than average;

- steamed bread: search peak value increased 376% compared to the average;

- Shopping: search peak is 382% higher than average;

- chest tightness: search peak increased 491% compared to the average;

- Fever: Search Peak 422% higher than average;

- symptoms of pneumonia: search peak increased by 1093% compared to the average;

- fear: Search Peak 183% higher than average;

- funeral homes: 212 per cent increase in peak-to-average searches;

These stay in the search engine behavior will not lie, suddenly raised curve behind, is one after another in the face of disaster helpless person.

Since writing these diaries, I've been getting more and more private messages from people in Wuhan telling me how he was quarantined, people taking pictures of boxes of food in the shelter, people complaining about the slackness of community work, some people share their grief over the loss of a loved one, others share their support for group buying, or they just send me the words Cheer Day After Day. I don't reply to every private message, but I keep what I see in my heart, this is the river and sea that we gather together, the water is billowing, the rabbit rises from the dark sink, every moment is unique.

I'm waiting for spring to bloom with all of you.

This is my diary of the siege of Wuhan, Day thirty-seven.
